In [[telecommunication]], '''desensitation''' is the reduction of desired [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signal]] [[Gain (electronics)|gain]] as a result of receiver reaction to an [[undesired signal]]. 

The gain reduction is generally due to [[Overcurrent|overload]] of some portion of the receiver (e.g., the [[automatic gain control]] circuitry) resulting in suppression of the desired signal because the receiver will no longer respond linearly to incremental changes in input voltage.

